# Wheesht Security Invariants

These must hold for every change to the backend (`main.py`, `models.py`) and the
client store/screens. Breaking one is a regression — add or update a test in
`tests/test_security.py` when touching the related area.

## Data isolation
- Every league-scoped query MUST filter by `league_id`. Never return another
  league's participants, chat, profiles, overrides or audit rows.

## Secrets
- Never return password or organiser hashes in any API response. Entries expose
  only a `hasPassword` boolean; Google identities expose only `hasGoogleLink`.
- Store secrets as PBKDF2 hashes (`_hash_password`). No plaintext comparisons.

## Authorisation
- All organiser writes go through `await _require_admin(session, league, token)`.
- Chat posts require proof of the author id: a session (`s1.`), account (`a1.`)
  or admin token — see `_chat_author_ok`. Never trust `author_id` alone.
- Protected-entry writes go through `_guard_account_write`.

## New endpoints
- Mutations that change a league must rate-limit (`_rate_limit`) and write a
  durable audit row (`_log_audit`) where an organiser action occurred.
- Destructive actions require explicit confirmation (exact code + name).

## Process
- Run `pytest tests/test_security.py` before any push touching auth, chat,
  organiser actions, isolation, or headers.
- Push to `main` only after the user confirms.
